Package nusri.fyp.demo.service.img_sender.roboflow

Class RoboflowService

java.lang.Object
nusri.fyp.demo.service.img_sender.roboflow.RoboflowService
@Service public class RoboflowService extends Object
Service class for interacting with Roboflow-based workflows, including synchronous and asynchronous image processing.
This class handles:
  • Sending Base64-encoded images to the Roboflow API for inference.
  • Processing responses to map predicted classes to appropriate ActionWithId or ObjectWithId entities.
  • Storing predictions as SinglePrediction (or AbstractActionObservation for generalized usage).
  • Testing pre-defined workflows via request calls, including describing the interface and running inferences.

Key points:
• Synchronous operations: sendImg(String, String, String, String) immediately returns a list of predictions.
• Asynchronous operations: sendImgAsync(String, String, String, String) returns a CompletableFuture that completes once Roboflow returns its results.
• Internal test methods (e.g., testPredefineWorkflowOnImage()) demonstrate usage of the Roboflow API for debugging or sample calls.

Depends on:
• RoboflowConfig for storing API credentials and relevant workflow information.
• RequestSenderOfOKHttp for sending HTTP requests to Roboflow.
• ObjectRepository and ActionRepository for looking up object/action names from the predicted class IDs.

  • Constructor Details

    • RoboflowService

      RoboflowService(RequestSenderOfOKHttp requestSenderOfOKHttp, ObjectRepository objectRepository, ActionRepository actionRepository, RoboflowConfig roboflowConfig, com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper objectMapper)
      Constructs the RoboflowService with required dependencies.
      This includes HTTP request handling, repositories for object/action lookups, and the Roboflow configuration.
      On initialization, it attempts to call several test routes (e.g., testPredefineWorkflow(RequestSenderOfOKHttp, RoboflowConfig, String, String)) to confirm API availability and log relevant data.
      Parameters:
      requestSenderOfOKHttp - The HTTP request sender for Roboflow API requests
      objectRepository - The repository used for mapping object IDs to their names
      actionRepository - The repository used for mapping action IDs to their names
      roboflowConfig - The configuration containing API credentials and settings for Roboflow
      objectMapper - The object mapper (not currently stored, but used during initialization)
      See Also:
      • RoboflowConfig
      • RequestSenderOfOKHttp

    • sendImg

      public List<SinglePrediction> sendImg(String base64String, String workspace_name, String workflow_name, String workflow_id)
      Synchronously sends a Base64-encoded image to Roboflow for inference.
      If successful, the predictions are mapped to SinglePrediction objects, with class IDs translated to human-readable names via objectRepository or actionRepository.
      Parameters:
      base64String - The Base64-encoded image to be sent to Roboflow
      workspace_name - The workspace name used in the Roboflow API request
      workflow_name - The workflow name used in the Roboflow API request
      workflow_id - The specific workflow ID used for inference
      Returns:
      A list of SinglePrediction objects extracted from Roboflow's response
      See Also:

    • sendImgAsync

      public CompletableFuture<List<AbstractActionObservation>> sendImgAsync(String base64String, String workspace_name, String workflow_name, String workflow_id)
      Asynchronously sends a Base64-encoded image to Roboflow for inference.
      Returns a CompletableFuture that completes once Roboflow responds with predictions, which are then converted into AbstractActionObservation objects for broader state machine compatibility.
      Parameters:
      base64String - The Base64-encoded image to be sent to Roboflow
      workspace_name - The workspace name used in the Roboflow API request
      workflow_name - The workflow name used in the Roboflow API request
      workflow_id - The specific workflow ID used for inference
      Returns:
      a CompletableFuture holding a list of AbstractActionObservation after inference
      See Also:
